        "subtype": "bot_message",
        "text": "*[Bug 19019] interaction() should warn when coalescing levels*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19019>\n\nSebastian Meyer (<mailto:seb.meyer@fau.de|seb.meyer@fau.de>) changed:\n\n           What    |Removed                     |Added\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                 CC|                            |seb.meyer@fau.de\n\n--- Comment #3 from Sebastian Meyer (<mailto:seb.meyer@fau.de|seb.meyer@fau.de>) ---\n(In reply to Robert Schlicht from comment #0)\n&gt; \n&gt;     ave(3:4, c(1.0, 1.5), c(5.5, 5.0))\n&gt; \n&gt; which should return `3 4`, but returns `3.5 3.5`.\n\nNote that under `options(OutDec = \",\")`, it does return the expected result ...\nThis is of course related to character conversion and `interaction`'s default\n`sep=\".\"`.\n\n&gt; The issue is the same as\n&gt; the one mentioned on the help page for `split` at the end of the Details\n&gt; section.\n\nRight, the same unlucky grouping can arise even with factor input when the\nlevels include a dot:\n\n```\n&gt; f1 &lt;- factor(c(\"a.\", \"a\"))\n&gt; f2 &lt;- factor(c(\"b\", \".b\"))\n&gt; interaction(f1, f2, drop = TRUE) |&gt; levels()\n[1] \"a..b\"\n&gt; droplevels(f1:f2) |&gt; levels()  # i.e., sep = \":\"\n[1] \"a:.b\" \"a.:b\"\n```\n\nI am not sure about the suggestion of adding a warning in `interaction` (and\nthen also `:`) when level combinations are merged. It would be good to know if\nthis already happens in some examples and is used as a feature.\n\nRegarding `ave`: As the actual labels of the interaction are irrelevant in\n`ave`, it could at least use a different separator that is less likely to occur\nin the input labels. A semicolon avoids the issue with numeric grouping codes,\nbut we could also use something like `\"_:_\"`.",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1773574711.174209",
        "bot_id": "B06769YJX9Q",
