                        ],
                        "contains_padding": true
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nRight, the same unlucky grouping can arise even with factor input when the\nlevels include a dot:\n\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "> f1 <- factor(c(\"a.\", \"a\"))\n> f2 <- factor(c(\"b\", \".b\"))\n> interaction(f1, f2, drop = TRUE) |> levels()\n[1] \"a..b\"\n> droplevels(f1:f2) |> levels()  # i.e., sep = \":\"\n[1] \"a:.b\" \"a.:b\"\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nI am not sure about the suggestion of adding a warning in "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "interaction",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " (and\nthen also "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ":",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ") when level combinations are merged. It would be good to know if\nthis already happens in some examples and is used as a feature.\n\nRegarding "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "ave",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ": As the actual labels of the interaction are irrelevant in\n"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "ave",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ", it could at least use a different separator that is less likely to occur\nin the input labels. A semicolon avoids the issue with numeric grouping codes,\nbut we could also use something like "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\"_:_\"",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
