        "text": "*[Bug 19019] interaction() should warn when coalescing levels*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19019>\n\n--- Comment #4 from Elin Waring (<mailto:elin.waring@gmail.com|elin.waring@gmail.com>) ---\nYes I tested changing the separator, that helps.\n\nHowever, isn't it strange that using quotation marks when calling interaction\neven when the variable is a factor gives a different result than when not using\nquotation marks?  Even in the comment 3 example, if you change it to \n\n```\nf1 &lt;- c(\"a.\", \"a\")\n f2 &lt;- c(\"b\", \".b\")\n\n```\n\nYou get different results. \n\n&gt; [1] a..b a..b\n&gt;Levels: a..b a...b a.b",
