        "subtype": "bot_message",
        "text": "*[Bug 19019] interaction() should warn when coalescing levels*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19019>\n\n--- Comment #5 from Robert Schlicht (<mailto:robert.schlicht@tu-dresden.de|robert.schlicht@tu-dresden.de>) ---\nInterestingly, `:` does not merge levels and returns an invalid factor (as in\n`.valid.factor`):\n```\n[1] a::b a::b\nLevels: a::b a:b a:::b a::b\nWarning message:\nIn print.factor(x) : duplicated level [4] in factor\n```\n\nThe merging for `interaction` was apparently added in version 2.9.1 in 2009\n(and later fixed in version 2.11.1). The NEWS at\n<https:\/\/cran.r-project.org\/doc\/manuals\/NEWS.2> mentions \"interaction() now\nensures that the levels of the result are unique.\"\n\nI do not fully understand the use case for merging, instead of stopping with an\nerror message, but it was probably done like that for a reason.\n\nRegarding comment #4, I suspect the difference is due to the `drop` argument.",
